text: There is a 6 GB per 24-hour period upload or download data transfer limit starting at midnight of each day, on all of your combined traffic on ResNet and UIC wireless
FTP and SFTP servers are allowed by the University firewall
The network firewall does prevent some applications from working in their normal manner, for example, video and audio conferencing products that use the H.323
Sony Playstation 2 is allowed by the University firewall
University Housing monitors only the amount of traffic
Everquest is blocked by the University firewall
You may not run any services (e.g., FTP services,listservers,P2P file sharing servers, publishing files via generic file services, etc.) via ResNet or NYURoam wireless networks
The system passively monitors the network throughput when traffic is light
Housing does not normally limit the amount of bandwidth
SMTP is allowed by the University firewall
MSN audio and video are not allowed by the University firewall, but the MSN chat, application sharing and file transferring are not blocked
Students have 200 GB of Free monthly usage
